fields: See you later! I'm so late!
I live a normal life, attending a normal school in a normal town.
'Sup, Yoshitake? The hell are you eating?!
That's no good. You're obviously supposed to eat bread when you're running late.
I don't even know where to start with that!
Come, mobile suits. We heroes will be your opponents.
Yeah, since when do you  get to be in the center?
Well, it's 'cause I heard that Square and Sunrise were doing a collab.
This is an anime about normal everyday life!
Mobile suits and tales of adventure don't come into it!
Hey, how do you get a girlfriend?
Well, you see, in the classroom after school, a girl is distributing handouts by herself.
Well, what would you do, Tadakuni?
Hey, I need to lock up the classroom.
Do you need to finish that up today?
Y-Yeah, the teacher asked me to...
I'll help you, so give me half.
Or perhaps you were waiting for my special  lesson, Tadakyuni?
S-Somehow, a female teacher barged into the scene!
I'm doing this for you! Deal with it!
I'm going home. Goodbye. H-Hey, wait!
There's a lot of characters, so you just have to go with the flow!
How am I supposed to go along with that ?!
I don't really need help. You need to get to your club, don't you?
It's way more important than the acting!
Don't be so fussy! I mean, what are we even doing?
Man, this is all messed up.
It's not like I really wanted to know how to get a girlfriend, anyway...
I just kind of asked, so why did things turn out like this?
I wonder if I should leave the class president for now and handle the other one first.
Hey, are you free? If you'd like, please come with me to...
Let's give up, Tadakuni. I can't put up with this, either.
Huh? Come on, I'm not the class pres...
No, Pres. Just come with me!
Run, Tadakuni! Leave behind your tsundere childhood friend!
Throw out your little sister who's unrelated by blood!
Hold on to that hand, and just, just... keep running!
I wanted to show you this scenery.
I'm impressed. You should be able to get most girls with that.
But we're at an all-boys school.
Hidenori. On the Modern Jap exam, what did you put for number four?
Does comparing answers even matter now?
You're always hanging around my house.
Don't you have anything better to do?
We've got time to kill after our final period exams, so whatever.
Hey, Yoshitake. I was just wondering... what do you think of skirts?
Let's not even go there, man. First of all
Don't start an argument now! Go home already!
But it's just a roll of cloth around your waist!
It doesn't hide anything, I suppose.
No, it's a splendid piece of clothing that's been around since the Middle Ages!
Even so, you walk around with your underwear exposed!
It leaves you defenseless, and it's shameful!
Can we borrow your sister's skirts?
I found them. She'll kill you!
That's my little sister's underwear, dude!
Rest assured. It's tit for tat. I left my underwear behind in its stead.
All right, hurry and put it on!
Hey, aren't we supposed to put these on from the bottom?
She's really gonna get mad at me, so cut it out!
Oh, our leg hair! What are we gonna do about our leg hair? It doesn't matter!
Idiot! It's fine to have leg hair!
What was that, you bastard? What's your problem?
It doesn't even matter anymore, so just put them on already!
Did you really want to wear it that much, you pervert?
I'm just sick of trying to reply to your idiocy!
H-Hey, wait. Are we seriously doing this?
Did you put it on? Yeah.
Couldn't you earn money doing this?
I'm not kidding, you look really good! Have more confidence!
That's great, Tadakuni! You not only changed your mind, but your personality too!
Let's turn it up a notch!
I was eating at a restaurant the other day.
I don't know what school she was from, but I saw a really cute girl.
She was eating a fish set. I was eating udon.
She got up after a while, but...
For some reason, on that neatly cleared bowl...
Something scary that happened to me, huh?
No, we aren't telling ghost stories here.
As you already know, I'm concerned about the hair on my nipples.
I wasn't getting anywhere pulling them one at a time with tweezers.
That's when... I saw the razor that my dad left lying around in the bathroom.
I thought: "I know! I'll get rid of them all at once with this!"
That's a painful story, not a scary story!
I wonder if nipples grow back.
Just go see a doctor already!
Something scary that happened to me, is it?
The other day, I spent the night at Kugikiho's place with some friends.
We got too crazy and drank a ton.
So of course, I helped him out by taking him to the bathroom.
Well, for some reason, there was a centipede in it!
Okay then, it's Hidenori's turn again.
C-Can we leave off right there?
I, uh... need to use the bathroom.
Did he stop somewhere, or something?
It seems like a pleasant scene at first glance, but he's averting his gaze.
It's proof that the conversation got cut off.
And they're walking at different speeds. It's proof that they don't yet know each other's pace.
Oh! That's Motoharu the delinquent for you.
Judging by this, we can surmise that it hasn't been long since they've met, and that they aren't going out.
But, that's only a matter of time. Which means...
You know what we need to do, right?
All of you, maximize your virgin power!
Hey, Motoharu. Sorry I'm late. I wasn't feeling good today...
It's cold today. Do you know why?
What? I don't get it. Does your head have a loose spring?
You've realized it by now, right?
Now then, who's that cute girl you're with?
Oh, it was nothing. If you keep going straight, you'll see the station.
Well, how was I supposed to know they weren't a couple?
What the heck is he saying?
But this wind is weeping just a little.
It seems as though the wind blew something unpleasant into town.
Let us make haste, lest the wind ceases.
The potato chips at that convenience store are half-off! Let's get going!
Oh, so you wrote a novel?
I see. "A love story of a boy and girl meeting at a riverbank".
The main character uses the power of the wind.
It's surprisingly similar to the current situation.
So basically, this girl wanted to turn her fantasy into a reality...
and chose me as the protagonist, so she sat near me.
Well, that's okay and all, but the problem is...
she gave this protagonist a particular background.
that I look like an introverted, lonely otaku?!
Yeah, yeah. Random stuff up next week.
Yeah, me too. It's awesome! Right?
It sounds different from a guitar.
Don't come at me from behind.
And thus, Tadakuni began his quest to become the strongest swordsman.
I'm not questing, and nothing's beginning.
There's no point if you don't equip your weapon.
But it sure is a nice stick.
Why have I been taking damage?!
What? Is it because I was holding the sword like this?
Hey, you. Are you headed to the town out west?
If so, take me with you.
I'm searching for a suitable human  to become the third demon lord
and oppose the other two demon lords who are fighting for possession of this world.
Don't make up some grandiose background story!
This'll end once we get home anyway!
Too long! What music was that?
You know, it's that music that plays in  RPGs when someone joins your party
Isn't it obvious, scum?  We're going to the King's castle first.
He called me scum! Just who is this guy?
My name is Jack. Enough of that.
We've arrived, boy. This is the castle.
Thank goodness you made it, heroes!
Why is everyone in the same pose?
You've seen through my disguise. I am the mid-boss.
I'm finished! The plot's moving too fast!
Somehow, we managed to defeat one of the demon lords.
The plot's progressing too fast since we're almost home!
Did we leave them back there?
I was wondering why you guys weren't holding anything.
One who possesses the ability to draw the  legendary sword has finally appeared, I see.
Nago, I want to ask you something.
What do high school girls find attractive about boys?
My friend told me that if someone says they like you, then you start liking them back.
But if she doesn't like his face, she'll turn him down regardless.
So it boils down to that, after all?
Why do you ask? Do you want to be popular?
Huh? What are you talking about? I-I'm already popular.
How about you, Yasunori? I'm popular.
I've been punched by a girl at a riverside before!
I have a question for you, too.
Why do high school guys just randomly start talking about themselves?
I'm sorry for doing that up till now.
We'll be more careful from now on.
You want me to praise you, or something?
You need to work on your appeal even more than I do.
Yeah. At least make an effort.
Yasunori, hand me that convex mirror.
Why do we even have one of these?
What's with the cheerful pose?  More like, who was that?
Going back to what we were saying,  the face doesn't make the
Jeez, you guys are annoying. Let's just say I lost, so get back to work!
Do you think we'll get to meet the girl in the mirror again?
Probably not. But I won't give up.
You guys stole my underwear again!
Shut up! If you don't die right now, I'll kill you!
If you don't wanna get killed, then die!
How many times do we have to die?
Well, we borrowed them one time to play around with, but this really wasn't us.
Liar! Then find out who did it!
I'm sure it just blew away in the wind.
And so, we're staking it out.
This is ridiculous. We won't find any culprit.
What are you doing, you pervert?
Yeah, it's true! I took it!
Sorry! Tadakuni and Hidenori stole them, too!
The wind always snatches away what's precious to me.
Today's the day of the Clean Campaign.
We're picking up trash on Asahi Street until five.
Yeah, about that. Of course, I want to join in, but...
How would it look if a bunch of guys  were loitering around picking up trash?
We're taking part in a well-respected school tradition that everyone in this area loves.
Let me see our school pamphlet for a minute.
Seems like there's too many useless school events in there.
I know that volunteering and orientation are important.
But what the hell is this "70 hour fast" thing?!
Who the hell thought of that?
It wasn't the student council, at least.
All right, I'm going to ask the principal.
What's the "70 hour fast" from this pamphlet about?
I don't know if it's a tradition or what, but please tell us the reason we do it.
Due to Sanada North Public High School's reduced enrollment, the school had fallen into crisis.
The principal at the time heard the cries of the students
and faced the prefecture alone, resolutely pleading his case for 70 hours straight.
And a miracle was said to have finally occurred.
And so, the school was saved...?
I can't believe something like that happened.
And we're supposed to learn from his great example?
You don't actually have to fast.
As long as you love this school  which he protected, that's enough.
To think that this school event had such a deep meaning behind it.
What do you want for dinner?
My friend said that she fights with her little brother all the time.
It's pretty rare, what we have!
Not many siblings get along, ya know?
My buddy has an older sister, too, but he pretty much hates her.
Did you know? Most entertainers get plastic surgery.
Oh, and there's another guy who has a little sister.
It seems he only talks to her about once a month.
Well, since our parents are never home, we siblings have to help each other out now, so doesn't it make sense that we get along?
We always used to play on this bank back when we were kids!
We played your favorite game, remember?
We really did do it. You were always pestering me to do it!
Yeah, I get it, we get along. Let's go shopping.
If you think you can do it with our height difference, just try it.
When I was brushing my teeth this morning...
I happened to look in the mirror, and there was some crap on my eyebrow.
I reached to brush it off, and then...
It seems it was a white eyebrow hair  that had grown to three centimeters.
Don't tell such a scary story!
Hey, you... Don't get full of yourself just because you told the scariest story last time. I'll win next time!
We may as well call Karasawa, since he's full of scary stories.
The other day, I was washing my face in the bath.
I was rubbing the facial cleanser in pretty hard with both hands...
a crunching sound echoed in my brain.
Damn, now I've done it! I thought. Blood slowly started dripping from my nose...
the blood suddenly stopped  dripping after just a couple seconds.
My nose was no longer bleeding, and the pain was gone.
In the end, nothing had actually happened.
Oh yeah, this isn't really a scary story, but...
He always wears a hat, right?
This really was just a coincidence, but...
I happened to see him taking his hat off once.
Man, that was pretty damn hilarious!
I don't think Karasawa would want other people to know.
Let's set up an ambush before he gets here! Yeah!
Hey, you called me over here, so  what's with the rough treatment?
At this point, I can't tell them I made that up...
I don't wanna! I don't wanna go!
You mustn't skip school without reason.
I don't wanna go! It's a pain in the butt!
How many times do you think I've gone?!
It should be fine if I skip one day!
No, school is not that kind of place.
You should correct that line of thinking.
No! I said I'm not going!
Milady! You mustn't yell so loudly!
Your false tooth will fall out!
Who has a false tooth? What are you talking about?
I know! You guys think of something.
Think up a good reason for me to skip school.
How about... because you caught a cold.
That's too common, and it won't hold! Next.
You can't skip school because of that! Next!
Because your false tooth fell out.
Why do you want me to have a false tooth so badly?
You're all useless! Be serious about this.
How about... your leg hair became difficult to manage?
Because there's a massive amount of salted fish entrails in your lunch every day.
What kind of a household do you think this is?!
Huh? You'd just mention that false tooth again.
I was? What are you getting at?
I've had enough of you guys! One more time!
Because you fought with *** Imada, your best friend.
Hey, don't make fun of my friends!
You didn't have to mention *** Imada by name!
Am I supposed to be *** Imada now?!
Its like you've all just given up on thinking!
Do it right! I'll work you to death!
Yeah, that's right! It's a false tooth. Got somethin' to say?
Hey! Stop it! Stop, stop it!
I've had enough! I'm going to school! Where's my Fixodent?!
Next episode's the long-awaited summer vacation!
You know, it's kind of strange for a school anime to start in summer.
Yeah, it'd be in spring, normally.
Normally, you'd start with an entrance ceremony or the start of a new semester.
And the "transfer student" setup would be pretty normal too, right?
So why exactly did we start this by lounging around at a friend's place?
Like I keep telling you, this isn't a school anime, it's an everyday anime.
Why are you all still wearing your uniforms? Well, I am, too.
But jeez, we've got quite the group here.
All the innocents are gathered together.
Is that okay?! Are you fine with that?!
No, it's not fine at all!
Well... It's fun to spend time with bros...
It's fun to spend time with bros.
Do you punks have any idea what you're doing?
If you get it, then get a girlfriend!
Now then, let's begin our meeting to discuss summer plans.
Come on. I finally got your spirits up.
I'll take anyone but you! Call Karasawa! Make him  the chairman!
Karasawa?! Can you come over to Tadakuni's in your uniform?
This is awful. It's a sausage fest, even though it's summer vacation.
Shut up! It doesn't really matter, does it?
I'm begging you, please don't bring us down any further!
It doesn't bother me at all!
Let's hear your thoughts, Tadakuni's sister. About what?
If you were to date someone from this bunch, who would it be?
She has a good eye. Sit here.
Please stop that. I misjudged you!
Hey, wait! It was just a joke! A joke!
Hey, don't bully Karasawa. Ow, ow, ow!
Now then, let's get back on topic.
Why aren't you guys hanging out with any girls, even though it's summer vacation?
Why are you  still the chairman?
Pay close attention. So where should we go this vacation? Any opinions?
Why am I the only one wearing the school trunks?
Why are you following school rules so strictly?
Just leave him be, it's time for us to pick up some bikini babes!
That's Karasawa for you. You found a great inn.
There's a lot of steam. There's too much of it!
What did you do at the beach?
What do you think he said? Hot guys and noodles?
How'd you know? Enough about that!
Hey, they have a ping pong table!
So basically, if you get the question right, you hit the ball?
If we're gonna play, let's decide on a penalty for the loser.
How about... you have to punch the Student Council president?
If you miss three times, you pay the penalty.
H-Hey, hold on, isn't this a bit too difficult?!
You guys decided these ahead of time, didn't you?!
Enough, I'll put an end to this.
Names of countries that have a moon in their flag!

The radio program by teens, for teens, about teens.
I, Hidenori, will be your host.
And today, I have with me a wonderful guest.
How has your work been going lately?
Oh, whatever. What's with your character?
This program is brought to you by Square-Enix.
Let's take a look at our first postcard here.

Um... Basically, other than scolding them and asking them to do chores, mothers don't really talk to their sons.
Naturally, the son will get a bad attitude.
Mothers should say more things that will make their sons happy.
Well, honestly, I wanted you to make a joke about it.

Why do high school boys dress so sloppily? is his question.
Certainly, collared shirts and slacks do leave a sloppy impression.
Because mothers buy them too large.
Yes. Any problems with high school boys can generally be traced back to their mothers.
Because they were originally part of their mothers.
The hell are you talking about?
Looks like our time is almost up!
Yosshii hasn't gotten a hold of his character, you see.
But we're planning on inviting a really amazing guest for next time.
This was Talking FS, brought to you by Hidenori and Yosshii.
Let's have fun until we puke!
So we don't have any regrets.
Tomorrow? Let's see... Where should we go?
Today's September 4th! Summer vacation's long over!
S. Swine. H-Hey, why are we playing shiritori?
It's finally the end of summer.
It felt kind of short, somehow.
Hey, I'm not doing this anymore!
That's the story. What do you think?
Just give it up. She won't understand that you're being kind.
There's a hair growing from your mole.
Hey. How do you get a boyfriend?
Why are you talking about something so shameful?!
Anyways, let's do something, since we've got time to kill. Okay?
Because we are high school girls!
A rock band, a jazz band, karate, kendo, mahjong, pretending to be cyborgs, or synchronized swimming!
High school boys, on the other hand, are just... pitiful!
Even though they suck at everything but sports and fighting, an anime about everyday life is having them to do stupid things!
I feel sorry for those high school boys...
Habata, can you borrow your brother's uniform?
Because high school girls are funny, no matter what they do.
Sounds fun! I'll go see if I can!
Next time, new characters come in one after another.
So then, a fish person appeared, and it turned out to be the older brother.
Oh... so it was the little brother who died in the accident, after all?
By the way, the Democratic party... Yeah?
What are you scared of? Let's go!
This is my first time going inside an all-boys school.
It's because of stuff like that that boys look down on us.
Huh? Are we being looked down on?
Well, I don't really know, but today, I'll show them how dignified we high school girls are compared to them.
Those good for nothing, empty-headed high school boys!
So we mistook a delinquent hangout for the Student Council room?

you should all be wearing visitor's passes.

Someone go some buy some better snacks.
No! I'm not talking about the teacake!

Vice President, I am the one who invited these girls here!
I have no clue where this idea came from, but the higher-ups want us to do it together with East High.
So I called them here for a meeting.
Well, you should really tell us this kind of thing in advance.
Anyway, I'm looking forward to working with you, Miss East High Student Council President.
Dammit! I'm getting made fun of from every direction here!
We'll definitely beat you at the Cultural Festival!
Why is this Ringo girl so mad?

so we put some effort into making this one!

it'll be my victory, won't it?

I will not do as you wish!
Please do not think of me as a child forever!
I am already moving towards a distant future!
Our culture clubs are really talented!
Now, I shall head out on a journey!
Farewell! Until the day we meet again!

Ringo. Won't you give it a rest?
Could you not bring your ugly pride into it?

We need to take it while it's ripe!
Let's dispense with the pleasantries and make it perfectly clear who's right and who's wrong!
It's a sure win for me, though.

Student Council President! Stay on your feet!

since it's carrying the weight of your souls.
You know, I... don't hit girls...

Yeah. That may be true. I'll try dealing with this in my own way.

Well, I'm a girl, so I don't really get it, but I think how they try too hard to act cool is pretty lame.

You say it like it's not your problem, but one of those stereotypical guys is living right next to us.
Why do you try so hard to live?
How dare you! Get your ass down here!

Yeah, that would explain a lot.

I'm the editor in charge of Yamauchi.

Excuse me, could you please quiet down while inside the restaurant?
I already told you it was your turn to pay, you bastard!
It's your fault for ordering the dried abalone!
Enough! Come with me to the office!
That should be enough. You're free to go!
All right, since we're free to go, let's pound some mochi!
Crap, I got mochi in my eyes!
If I'm going down, I'm taking you with me!
And thus, the world was saved.

What do you want for dinner tonight?

Wow, you two don't look anything alike!

Hey, why are you growing a beard?
It doesn't really matter, does it?
Watch your mouth around your elders, idiot!
Mino, you really get along well with him!
Wait, doesn't he look like that comedian?
You know, that guy who goes "Bobiin!"
Hey, Eikura! Say "Bobiin" for us. Just once is fine!
Come on, just say it. We won't laugh.
Sis... I'm going home ahead of you.
What are you taking about? You're coming, too!
We have to buy the hot pot ingredients!

You want to borrow our school's equipment?
Yes. I know it is a great inconvenience, but...
